With effect from 1 Oct 2016, the Infocomm Development Authority and the Media Development Authority were restructured to form the Info-communications Media Development Authority and the Government Technology Agency of Singapore.
INTERNATIONAL TELEPHONE CALL MINUTES - This figure includes total retail outgoing international call minutes as well as transit minutes and includes all Service-Based Operators (SBO).

TOTAL FIXED LINE SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - With effect from August 2008, data are updated on a quarterly basis, in March, June, September and December.  Fixed Lines includes Direct Exchange Lines ('DEL') and IP Telephony subscriptions using Level '6' numbers.

RESIDENTIAL FIXED LINE SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - With effect from August 2008, data are updated on a quarterly basis, in March, June, September and December.  Fixed Lines includes Direct Exchange Lines ('DEL') and IP Telephony subscriptions using Level '6' numbers.

CORPORATE/BUSINESS FIXED LINE SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - With effect from August 2008, data are updated on a quarterly basis, in March, June, September and December.  Fixed Lines includes Direct Exchange Lines ('DEL') and IP Telephony subscriptions using Level '6' numbers.

TOTAL MOBILE PHONE SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - Total Mobile Subscriptions includes 3G and 4G subscriptions (including both pre-paid and post-paid).  Statistics for 3G and 4G subscriptions are collected from May 2005 and March 2013 respectively onwards.  With effect from April 2017, total Post-paid and Pre-paid Subscriptions (2G) has ceased service and it will only include 3G and 4G subscriptions (including both pre-paid and post-paid).

TOTAL SUBSCRIPTIONS (3G), AT END OF PERIOD - Prior to November 2007, data cover post-paid subscriptions.  With effect from November 2007, data include pre-paid and post-paid 3G subscriptions.  Figures prior to December 2009 comprise both pre-paid and post-paid 3G subscriptions combined.  Data breakdown for pre-paid and post-paid 3G subscriptions are available with effect from December 2009.

TOTAL DIAL-UP INTERNET SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - The first commercial Internet service, Singnet, was launched in July 1994.  Figures prior to 1995 exclude subscriptions from academic, government and R & D organisations.  From 2001, figures include contributions from Internet Access Service Providers (IASPs).  From February 2000, figures include fixed-line subscribers offered free Internet access by Singtel.  With effect from April 2008, data cover paid Internet access subscriptions only, following the cessation of free dial-up Internet access offered by service providers by 31 March 2008.

TOTAL BROADBAND INTERNET SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - With effect from April 2007, Total Broadband Subscriptions (i.e. for connection speeds equal to, or greater than, 256 kbit/s, in one or both directions) includes retail xDSL, cable modems, leased line Internet, 3G, 3.5G/HSDPA, 4G/LTE, WiMAX or its equivalent and Wi-Fi hotspots access (including Wireless@SG subscriptions).

TOTAL WIRELESS BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - Total Wireless Broadband Subscriptions includes all retail broadband Internet access subscriptions (i.e., for connection speeds equal to, or greater than, 256 kbit/s, in one or both directions) provided via wireless platforms such as 3G, 3.5G/HSDPA, 4G/LTE,WiMAX or its equivalent and Wi-Fi hotspots (including Wireless@SG subscriptions).
TOTAL NON-WIRELESS BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD

RESIDENTIAL WIRED BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - Total Residential Wired Broadband includes all retail residential wired broadband subscriptions (i.e. for connection speeds equal to, or greater than, 256 kbit/s, in one or both directions) provided over xDSL, cable modems, leased line and optical fibre.  Residential wireless broadband subscriptions will be excluded.

CORPORATE WIRED BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD - Total Corporate Wired Broadband includes all retail corporate wired broadband subscriptions (i.e. for connection speeds equal to, or greater than, 256 kbit/s, in one or both directions) provided over xDSL, cable modems, leased line and optical fibre.  Corporate wireless broadband subscriptions will be excluded.
TOTAL NON-WIRELESS BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTIONS, AT END OF PERIOD
TOTAL XDSL - Total xDSL includes residential and corporate xDSL subscriptions.
TOTAL CABLE MODEM - Total Cable Modem includes residential and corporate cable modem subscriptions.

TOTAL OPTICAL FIBRE BROADBAND SUBSCRIPTION (I.E., OFFERED VIA PON OR ACTIVE ETHERNET) - Total Optical Fibre Broadband includes residential and corporate subscriptions to broadband Internet services using optical fibre networks, including end-to-end optical fibre broadband subscriptions that are offered via passive optical network ('PON') and Active Ethernet.

TOTAL SUBSCRIPTIONS USING OTHER BROADBAND INTERNET ACCESS PLATFORMS - From Nov 2010 to May 2011, the Total Broadband Subscriptions using other Broadband Internet Access Platforms included Fibre Broadband Subscriptions.  With effect from June 2011, this indicator will exclude Fibre Broadband Subscriptions.  Instead, Fibre Broadband Subscriptions will be reflected under a new and standalone indicator known as 'Total Optical Fibre Broadband Subscriptions'.
